#Osteoarthritis  Definition: Also called degenerative joint disease, is a chronic, slowly progressive, erosive damage to joint surfaces
#Osteoarthritis ; this loss of articular cartilage causes increasing pain with minimal or absent inflammation
#Osteoarthritis The incidence of degenerative joint disease is proportional to increasing age and trauma to the joint.
#Osteoarthritis Modest recreational running does not cause DJD, but playing contact sports with trauma does. Obesity increases DJD
#Osteoarthritis  Presentation: DJD is most commonly symptomatic in weight bearing joints (knee, hip, ankle).
#Osteoarthritis The hand is affected, but is not as great a cause of disability.
#Osteoarthritis Distal interphalangeal joints are more commonly affected in the hand

#Osteoarthritis  Effusion is rare. Stiffness is of short duration (under 15 minutes).
#Osteoarthritis DIP enlargement is Heberden nodes. PIP enlargement is Bouchard nodes
#Osteoarthritis The most accurate test is radiography of the affected joint.
#Osteoarthritis X-rays show joint space narrowing, #osteophytes, dense subchondral bone, and bone cysts
#Osteoarthritis Weight loss and moderate exercise; Acetaminophen: best initial analgesic
#Osteoarthritis NSAIDS: used if symptoms are not controlled with acetaminophen; second because of toxicity particularly GI bleeding
#Osteoarthritis Capsaicin cream, Intraarticular steroids if other medical therapy does not control pain, Joint replacement if severe
